Using the Gram-Schmidt process, we have $e{_{1}} = \begin{bmatrix}
0\\ 
1\\ 
0\\ 0
\end{bmatrix}
e{_{2}} = \begin{bmatrix}
\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\\ 
0\\ 
\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\\ 0
\end{bmatrix}
e{_{3}} = \begin{bmatrix}
1\\ 
0\\ 
0\\ -2
\end{bmatrix}
-0.5\begin{bmatrix}
1\\ 
0\\ 
1\\ 0
\end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix}
\frac{1}{3\sqrt{2}}\\ 
0\\ 
-\frac{1}{3\sqrt{2}}\\ -\frac{2\sqrt{2}}{3}
\end{bmatrix}$
